<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2015-10-10</DATELINE><TITLE>Hospital Systems Management</TITLE><BODY>All concepts of hospitals systems including professional standards, ethics, quality improvement, and resource utilization are covered in this chapter. The structure of successful hospitalist programs is used as a template. Then tools utilized for quality improvement, which have been adopted from other industries, are discussed as well. The transition to post-acute care and the complications encountered are examined in this chapter.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>